'''Eric Javier Davis Grajales''' (born 31 March 1991) is a Panamanian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|left-back]] for [[C.D. Plaza Amador|Plaza Amador]] and the [[Panama national football team|Panama national team]].

==Club career==
===Árabe Unido===
In 2009, he signed for [[Liga Panameña de Fútbol]] club [[Club Deportivo Árabe Unido|Árabe Unido]] where he made 44 appearances.

===Fénix===
In mid-2011 he signed a new contract with [[Uruguayan Primera División]] club [[Centro Atlético Fénix]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://panamafutbol.com/?p=4749 |publisher=Panamafutbol |title=Eric Davis al Fénix de Uruguay |access-date=11 July 2012 |date=19 August 2011 |language=es |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110922054712/http://panamafutbol.com/?p=4749 |archive-date=22 September 2011 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He made his debut on 12 May 2012, playing 10 minutes against [[Club Sportivo Cerrito]].<ref>[https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2012/05/12/uruguay/primera-division/club-sportivo-cerrito/centro-atletico-fenix/1246425/] – Soccerway</ref>

In summer 2013, Davis joined [[Sporting San Miguelito]]<ref>[http://www.critica.com.pa/golazo/eric-davis-es-el-nuevo-fichaje-del-sportin-sm-277930 Eric Davis es el nuevo fichaje del Sportin SM] – Crítica {{in lang|es}}</ref> and he returned to Árabe Unido in summer 2015.<ref>[http://lpf.com.pa/w/el-arabe-en-busca-de-su-segundo-bicampeonato/ El Árabe buscará su segundo bicampeonato] – LPF {{in lang|es}}</ref>

===Dunajská Streda===
In September 2015, Davis signed a contract with [[Slovak Super Liga|Fortuna liga]] club [[FC DAC 1904 Dunajská Streda|Dunajská Streda]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://profutbal.sk/clanok/197401-V_Dunajskej_Strede_dalsi_Panamcan_|title=V Dunajskej Strede ďalší Panamčan|publisher=ProFutbal|date=11 September 2015|access-date=18 June 2018|language=sk|archive-date=9 April 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200409082102/https://profutbal.sk/clanok/197401-V_Dunajskej_Strede_dalsi_Panamcan_|url-status=dead}}</ref> He spent eight seasons with the club, making more than 140 league appearances and helping them secure several top-three finishes in the Slovak Super Liga, including runner-up finishes in [[2018–19 Slovak First Football League|2018–19]], [[2020–21 Slovak First Football League|2020–21]] and [[2022–23 Slovak First Football League|2022–23]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://dunajskostredsky.sk/eric-davis-dac-zostane-navzdy-v-mojom-srdci |title=Eric Davis: DAC zostane navždy v mojom srdci |publisher=Dunajská Streda |language=sk |date=25 May 2023 }}</ref>

===Later career===
Davis joined [[MLS]] side [[D.C. United]] in 2023,<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dcunited.com/news/d-c-united-ha-fichado-al-defensa-de-la-seleccion-panamena-eric-davis |title=D.C. United ha Fichado al Defensa de la Selección Panameña Éric Davis |publisher=D.C. United |language=es |date=3 August 2023 }}</ref> before returning to Slovakia with [[FC Košice (2018)|FC Košice]] in February 2024.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.laestrella.com.pa/deportes/futbol/eric-davis-es-el-nuevo-jugador-del-fc-kosice-de-eslovaquia-HF6052797 |title=Eric Davis es el nuevo jugador del FC Kosice de Eslovaquia |publisher=La Estrella de Panamá |language=es |date=6 February 2024 }}</ref> He subsequently moved to Brazilian club [[Vila Nova Futebol Clube|Vila Nova]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.prensa.com/deportes/eric-davis-sale-del-vila-nova-brasileno-tras-rescindir-contrato-de-mutuo-acuerdo/ |title=Eric Davis sale del Vila Nova brasileño tras rescindir contrato de mutuo acuerdo |publisher=La Prensa |language=es |date=28 May 2025 }}</ref> before returning to Panama to sign for [[C.D. Plaza Amador|Plaza Amador]] in July 2025.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rpctv.com/liga-panamena-futbol-lpf/futbol/eric-davis-es-presentado-como-nuevo-jugador-del-plaza-amador-n6046528 |title=Eric Davis es presentado como nuevo jugador del Plaza Amador |publisher=RPC TV |language=es |date=10 July 2025 }}</ref>

==International career==
Davis was part of the [[Panama national under-20 football team|Panama U-20]] squad that participated in the [[2011 CONCACAF U-20 Championship]] where he help his nation qualify to the [[2011 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[Colombia]].<ref>{{FIFA player|337232}}</ref>

His senior international debut for [[Panama national football team|Panama]] came on 11 August 2010 against [[Venezuela national football team|Venezuela]], in a [[friendly match]] played in [[Panama City]]<ref>{{NFT player|id=39574}}</ref> and he has, as of 8 June 2015, earned a total of 19 caps, scoring no goals.

In 2011, he was called up for the [[2011 CONCACAF Gold Cup]] by [[Julio Dely Valdés]].<ref>[https://www.rsssf.org/tables/2011gc-full.html CONCACAF Championship, Gold Cup 2011 – Full Details] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130315040517/http://www.rsssf.com/tables/2011gc-full.html |date=15 March 2013 }} – RSSSF</ref> He played for Panama in the [[2015 CONCACAF Gold Cup]].

In May 2018, he was named in Panama's 23-man [[Panama national football team|squad]] for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] in Russia, where he played in two matches against [[England national football team|England]] and [[Tunisia national football team|Tunisia]] as Panama were knocked out at the Group Stage.<ref>{{cite web| url = https://www.goal.com/en-gb/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb| title = Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad – Final 23-man lists {{!}} Goal.com}}</ref>

In May 2026, he was selected in Panama's 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fepafut.com/blog/2026/05/26/los-26-mundialistas-de-panama/ |title=Los 26 Mundialistas de Panamá |trans-title=Panama's 26-Man World Cup Squad |publisher=[[Panamanian Football Federation]] |date=May 26, 2026 |access-date=May 26, 2026 |language=es |archive-date=May 26, 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260526170649/https://www.fepafut.com/blog/2026/05/26/los-26-mundialistas-de-panama/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

